the whole story. And I for one am satisfied with a pretty weak definition of
free will, a Turing Test version. If the organism acts like it has free will, it
has free will. The pure purposeful action free from subconscious or
environmental determinants, predispositions, or influence seems like a Platonic
ideal to me.

